call(bytes32,bytes).notice: Call the system at the given resourceSelector. If the system is not public, the caller must have access to the namespace or name (encoded in the resourceSelector).

callFrom(address,bytes32,bytes).notice: Call the system at the given resourceSelector on behalf of the given delegator. If the system is not public, the delegator must have access to the namespace or name (encoded in the resourceSelector).

installRootModule(address,bytes).notice: Install the given root module in the World. Requires the caller to own the root namespace. The module is delegatecalled and installed in the root namespace.

documentation.text:
The IBaseWorld interface includes all systems dynamically added to the World
 during the deploy process.
